deck: Shinobu, like her sister Mikoto, was raised to be a ninja by their mother, but she moved on to the path of the samurai. She's a clumsy girl who tends to get lost easily.
description:
Origin

Shinobu was born on the isolated Airan Island along with her two sisters, Kunai and Mikoto. They were trained from a young age by their mother Kokoro to be ninja. When all the girls of the island were young, their fathers all tragically died during a storm at sea while fishing. While inspired by a book she read, she strayed to follow the path of a samurai. During her travels across Airan Island, she found a young cow she named Beef Steak. As she started hearing from the various animal guardians about a young man named Ikuto that had recently arrived from the outside, she returned to the village to challenge him to a duel.

Creation

Shinobu (しのぶ, Shinobu) is a main character in the Nagasarete Airantou series that was created by Takeshi Fujishiro. The series first began serialization in Square Enix's Monthly Shōnen Gangan magazine in January 2002.

Her first appearance was in Nagasarete Airantou Volume 8 CH. 43 "Nin-Nin Shite".

Character Evolution

Major Story Arcs

Powers & Abilities

Though Shinobu is extremely clumsy, she has no problem recovering due to her extreme level of durability. Her strength of body allows her to recover quickly after falling.

Kendo

Shinobu has trained in sword techniques since she first became infatuated with samurai. Despite her impressive skill from self training, she went to Ikuto for training.

Ninjutsu

Shinobu was trained in various skills of ninjutsu by her mother. Part of this training also included hand-to-hand combat.

Super Speed

As part of Shinobu's ninja training, she learned how to move at incredible speed for short bursts. This is helpful in combat for getting behind her opponent to strike before they can notice her. However, this speed can work against her due to her natural clumsiness.

Poison Resistance

While growing up, Shinobu and her sisters were slowly trained by their mother in resistance to a wide variety of poisons. Kokoro gave them all small doses of poisons slowly as they grew up. This made them immune to various drugs.

Shadow Clones

A special technique that Shinobu likes to use is her ability to create physical clones of herself. When up against a formidable opponent, she will create eight clones to overpower her target with numbers. Sadly, they are still just an clumsy as the original.

Weapons & Equipment

Other Media

Anime

Nagasarete Airantou (2007)

The Nagasarete Airantou anime series is the second direct adaptation of Takeshi Fujishiro's original manga. This series is produced by Feel and first began airing in April 4, 2007. Shinobu's first anime appearance was in Nagasarete Airantou - Episode 18 "Let's Have A Match, Ninja", which aired on August 1. 2007. Her character in the Japanese series is voiced by Orie Kimoto.

Shinobu's introduction in the Nagasarete Airantou anime was changed for the original manga version. As well as her first meeting with Ikuto.
name: Shinobu

deck: Titan is a gigantic Atlantean monster and an enemy of the Avengers.
description:
Origin

Not much is known about Titan's origins or his relation to the Atlanteans or Sub-Mariner. All that is known is that Titan wishes to rule over the land and lay waste to any surface dwellers.

Creation

Titan was created by Dan Slott and Rafa Sandoval and first appeared in The Mighty Avengers #24.

Character Evolution

Titan has not featured much since his first appearance, his only other appearance was a cameo in The Mighty Avengers #35.

Major Story Arcs

Dark Reign

Titan randomly attacked Biarritz in France in pursuit of conquest of Earth. He was met by the Avengers (Amadeus Cho, Hercules, Quicksilver, Stature, U.S.Agent, Vision and Wasp) and G.R.A.M.P.A. agents Blackjack (Ace and One-Eyed Jacquie). It fell to Stature and Wasp to engage Titan and prevent him from reaching further in-land due to his immense size dwarfing over the rest of the Avengers and Blackjack.

Forced to grow to their absolute upper limit, Stature and Wasp battled Titan to the point where the beast had started to become weak due to having being away from water for too long. As the giants duked it out, Hercules and Vision attempted to blind the beast by having Vision fire a solar beam onto an enlarged mirror and directing the light into Titan's eyes. Alas, the attempt only enraged Titan who continued to fight Stature and Wasp.

Elsewhere, Amadeus, Blackjack and U.S.Agent armed themselves with an assortment of guns which would fire a special saline mix Amadeus had developed which would draw all the moisture out of Titan, thus further weakening him.

Titan attempted to flee to the sea to absorb some water and replenish his strength, battering off the attacking Avengers on his way. Using his super-speed to circle Titan, Quicksilver was able to make the monster lose his balance and fall off - thus defeating him. Titan was then taken into custody by G.R.A.M.P.A. and held within a special facility.

Powers and Abilities

Titan is a gigantic sea creature. Most of his power and strength stem from his size but as seen if he is away from water too long his strength begins to waver. Titan has multiple tentacles which he can use to further cause damage.
name: Titan

deck: Selah Burke is the daughter of the super villain Edward Lansky (Lightmaster). She is a young heroine that took on the mantle of "Sun Girl" and operates as a member of the New Warriors.
description:
Origin

Selah Burke is the daughter of former Empire State University professor Edward Lanksy, (also known as the super villain "Lightmaster") She is a young woman who splits her time as a college student and super-heroine. Selah utilizes light based gadgets and weaponry, designed by her father, and the code name "Sun Girl" to fight crime. She accredits Spider Man as the biggest inspiration for becoming a hero.

Creation

Sun Girl was created by Christopher Yost and David Lopez.

Major Story Arcs

Superior Spider-Man Team-Up

Sun Girl first appeared attempting to combat the Superior Spider-Man. She was infected by a virus (just as many other heroes were) after making contact with William Allen. The Superior Spider-Man fought against her and healed her from the virus. The "superior" Spider-Man is really Doctor Octopus who (unbeknownst to Sun Girl) placed his mind inside Peter Parker's body and is imposing as Spider-Man. He had been fighting other heroes infected by the virus all day, and eventually crossed paths with Sun Girl.

She later attempted to stop the Wrecking Crew from robbing a company called "Alchemax." She was quickly outnumbered until Superior Spider-Man showed up with his new team, the "Superior Six" ("reformed" version of the Sinister Six). They began to assist Sun Girl in combating the Wrecking Crew, who eventually escaped after knocking her unconscious. When she awoke, she found herself in Superior Spider-Man's hideout and he then began to question where she got her technology from. Apparently, she tells him and then ventures home.

The next day, Selah awakes in her apartment. She goes to a few classes and then contacts her father, who informs her that he was in the midst of doing something important (most likely villianry). Later, she grabs her light-suit and goes on patrol. While on patrol, Sun Girl encounters the Wrecking Crew and the new Masters of Evil. The Superior Spider-Man arrives to the scene with his "Superior Six," and Sun Girl joins them in fighting against the Masters of Evil. The leader of the Masters of Evil arrives and revealed himself to be Lightmaster.

Selah immediately recognized her father and was able to intercept his powerful light based attack with her own light blast, which knocked everyone unconscious. When she awoke shortly after, she realized that the Superior Spider-Man (and her father) had been captured by the Superior Six. The members of the Superior Six were initially brainwash by the Superior Spider-Man and had broken free of his control when Sun Girl and Lightmaster clashed. Sun Girl then manages to save her father and the Superior Spider-Man from danger. With the knowledge of Superior Spider-Man brainwashing the Sinister Six, Sun Girl gains a reformed and indifferent opinion towards Spider-Man being her hero.

Powers and Abilities

Powers

Sun Girl is an average human who possess no superhuman abilities. Instead, she utilizes a series of light-based weaponry and gadgets. She wears a special power suit and harness that allows her to fly and grants her enough durability to resist multiple attacks from the Wrecking Crew. She wields a pair of dual pistols, capable of blasting concussive beams. The guns can also be used to blind her enemies.
